<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-782-478  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 782 478.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  August 21 1989 v3 n34 p1(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Unisys lists work force, staff cuts.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Anthes, Gary H.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Unisys Corp is cutting its work force by 7 percent to 8 percentand reducing its annual costs by at least $400 million by the endof 1990.andP;  A complete review of its operations should be finishedby the end of Sep 1989, a move prompted by disappointing earnings.andO;The company is restructuring its US marketing operations andreducing manufacturing overhead.andP;  It is also accelerating a moveto in-house production of microprocessor systems and the use ofcommon parts and processes across product lines.andP;  The moves followa freeze on salaries and hiring in early Aug 1989.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Unisys Corp. (planning).andO;Ticker:    UIS.andO;Topic:     LayoffEmploymentPlanningLossesCost Reduction.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>